    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-21T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-21T03:00:00-05:00" n="207"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.003 Wallace, Henry A./45: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-21T15:00:00+07:00"
                            >April 21, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 21—1:13 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>695. Message from Mr. Wallace to Mme. Chiang has been delivered (your 521, April
                    18). Please inform Mr. Wallace that I shall be delighted to have him as my guest
                    for first evening and shall follow his wishes that evening not become a social
                    event but be spent with staff only.</p>
                <p>When place of Mr. Wallace’s first arrival in China becomes known Government will
                    probably as usual send representative, likely Hollington Tong,<note n="26"
                        xml:id="d207fn26">Chinese Vice Minister of Information.</note> to join him
                    there. I shall at same time send officer or Attaché of Embassy. I assume
                    Department will inform Mr. Wallace in outline of present conditions in China
                    before his departure.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
